<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-145] LFSCK Phase 1.5 - Enable dirdata before lfsck -t namespace when upgrading from 1.8-&gt;2.x </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-145</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, the manual section on using LFSCK to do the fid-in-dirent and linkEA updates does not include any reference to enabling dirdata on the MDT before doing LFSCK -t namespace. (Command to check and repair fid-in-dirent and linkEA)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My understanding is that this is a necessary step before using lfsck to add/repair fid-in-dirent and linkEA.  Presumably the manual should explain this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, I&apos;m not sure if LFSCK will do the right thing if it is started with -t namespace when dirdata is disabled.  I&apos;m putting a question about this in the LFSCK Phase 1.5 ticket:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.hpdd.intel.com/browse/LU-1866&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://jira.hpdd.intel.com/browse/LU-1866&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.hpdd.intel.com/browse/LUDOC-85&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://jira.hpdd.intel.com/browse/LUDOC-85&lt;/a&gt; for documentation changes already made for LFSCK Phase 1.5.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This may be a partial dupe of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.hpdd.intel.com/browse/LUDOC-68&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://jira.hpdd.intel.com/browse/LUDOC-68&lt;/a&gt;, but this does not reference LFSCK fid-in-dirent and linkEA updates.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
